1. Creates three observer nodes using `std::make_shared`
2. Gets the observer graph instance using `ObserverGraph::getInstance()`
3. Sets up the chain relationships using `graph.addObserver()` - observer2 observes observer1, observer1 observes target
4. Notifies the target by calling `valueChanged(true)`
5. Verifies both observers were notified by checking their call counts
6. Calculates the total call count by summing observer1 and observer2 call counts
7. Returns a pair containing the total call count and a boolean indicating if the chain notification worked correctly

The chain should work because when the target is notified, it will notify observer1, which will then notify observer2 due to the established observer relationships.

